item.title: [ENTESB-2460] ParallelAggregate option for camel multicast with parallel processing is not working
item.description: ParallelAggregate is implemented only for serial processing in MulticastProcessor.java. I do not know if it is necessary to support parallel aggregate for serial processing, but it is definitely missing for parallel processing, so the aggregator does not have to be thread-safe because it is called from synchronized method.
item.summary: ParallelAggregate option for camel multicast with parallel processing is not working

status.description: The issue is considered finished, the resolution is correct. Issues which are not closed can be reopened.

comments.comment:
ParallelAggregate is not working.

Each endpoint of multicast with parallelProcessing=true is called with own thread. But the aggregate logic is processed in private AggregateOnTheFlyTask class and its aggregateOnTheFly() method, which is called from new thread too. Bud the aggregation logic use only one new thread, so the doAggregateInternal (and so the client implementation of AggregationStrategy) for parallelAggregate=true option is called serially.

For that reason, the parallelAggregate option has no relevance because the client AggregationStrategy will never be called in parallel.
Ping me mid next week when I have had a chance to look at this again.
Claus Ibsen We have 6.2 code freeze wednesday, do you have time to get this in?
Václav , and well spotted the issue about it not being parallel in parallel mode

customfieldvalues.customfieldvalue:
You can reproduce the issue with this configuration:

<route>
 
	<from uri="direct:multicastParallelAggregate"/>
 
	<multicast parallelProcessing="true" parallelAggregate="true" strategyRef="parallelAggregate">
 
		<to uri="direct:a"/>
 
		<to uri="direct:b"/>
 
	</multicast>
 
</route>
 
 
 
<route>
 
	<from uri="direct:a"/>
 
	<setBody>
 
		<constant>A</constant>
 
	</setBody>
 
</route>
 
<route>
 
	<from uri="direct:b"/>
 
	<setBody>
 
		<constant>B</constant>
 
	</setBody>
 
</route>
 
 
 
<bean id="parallelAggregate" class="org.jboss.camel.ParallelAggregate"/>


public class ParallelAggregate implements AggregationStrategy {
 
 
 
	private static boolean invoked;
 
	private static boolean calledInParallel;
 
 
 
	public static boolean isCalledInParallel() {
 
		return calledInParallel;
 
	}
 
 
 
	public static void reset() {
 
		invoked = calledInParallel = false;
 
	}
 
 
 
	@Override
 
	public Exchange aggregate(Exchange oldExchange, Exchange newExchange) {
 
		System.out.println("A:" + new Date().toString());
 
		synchronized (this) {
 
			if (!invoked) {
 
				invoked = true;
 
			} else {
 
				calledInParallel = true;
 
			}
 
		}
 
		System.out.println("B:" + new Date().toString());
 
 
 
		// Simulate processing, another thread should access aggregator
 
		try {
 
			Thread.sleep(5000);
 
		} catch (InterruptedException e) {
 
			throw new RuntimeException(e);
 
		}
 
		// or like this
 
		// long t = new Date().getTime() + 10000;
 
		// while (t > new Date().getTime()) {
 
		// }
 
		System.out.println("C:" + new Date().toString());
 
 
 
		invoked = false;
 
		if (oldExchange == null) {
 
			return newExchange;
 
		}
 
		oldExchange.getIn().setBody(this.getClass().getName());
 
		return oldExchange;
 
	}
 
}
